---
description: Security and privacy rules
globs: ["src/**/*", "src-tauri/src/**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Security and privacy are product requirements.

Rules:
- do not expose secrets or API keys to the frontend unnecessarily
- do not log sensitive code content, tokens, or credentials
- require AI enablement before sending code/diff externally
- keep security-sensitive operations on the Rust/backend side
- sanitize any persisted settings related to secrets
- avoid insecure defaults

When implementing AI:
- assume some users are privacy-sensitive
- make external sharing intentional
- keep auditability and transparency in mind

Do not:
- hardcode tokens
- store secrets in plain unsafe locations if avoidable
- send more repository content than the user action requires